cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SI. 

The paper proposes a privacy-preserving algorithm for contextual bandits, which is a machine learning problem. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category. The paper also deals with privacy concerns, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The proposed algorithm involves collecting feedback from other local agents, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also uses synthetic benchmarks and real-world data, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), respectively.
